<dl id="n08048c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n08" href="#n08048c">N08 (VI.B.6)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n08all.htm#n08048c"> 48(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> penchant <small>Red</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n08048c"><li>FW 435.33 </li><li><a href="../../flex/qA/lexqA.htm#n08048c">2010</a> </li><li><a href="../../flex/qA/l39qA.htm#n08048c">1939</a> </li><li><ms href="#n08048c">MS BL 47482b-15v</ms> </li><li>JJA 57:032 <a name="qA1d" href="../../FF/fdra/qda.htm#qA1d">Usage</a> </li><li> <a href="../../flex/q/qA1d.htm#n08048c">Draft: III&sect;2A.1</a></li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources">Les grandes formes du mensonge sont toujours le produit d&apos;une accumulation de mauvais <mark>penchants</mark> et, par cons&eacute;quent, leur r&eacute;v&eacute;lation s&apos;obtient &agrave; l&apos;aide de plusieurs indices. <br><font color="green">[The major varieties of lying are always the result of the accumulation of bad traits and are revealed, consequently, through a number of signs.]</font> <small> J Cr&eacute;pieux-Jamin, <a name="JCJL" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#JCJL"><cite title="source">Les &eacute;l&eacute;ments de l'&eacute;criture des canailles</cite></a> (1923) 274</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
